600. Almone: the statue of Cy- bele was washed every year in the Almo.

605. augur: der. avi-ger.

602. Titiique sodales: an an- cient body of priests of Sabine origin.

603. Salius: the Salii were twelve priests of Mars.

605. effusam anfractibus: ‘ex- tending in straggling districts.'

606. fulminis ignes: i. e. res ficlmine tactas. The name of loci

rendered thus sacri, was bidental, so called from the offering (bidens).

608. electa cervice: i. e. tau- rum egregium. Weise.

609. obliquo: a difficulty is raised by commentators as to the meaning of this : Weise says it means ‘ with point downwards.’

622. hostili de parte: one por- tion of the entrails was marked out as indicating Pompey’s fate, the other Caesar'53 the latter is called, the pars hostilis.
